After creating aim_island, my first map, I got a private message from TempletonPeck asking to improve the map so he could place it on his gungame server. So I improved my map and here is the result:

- Removed the weapons+tables at both spawns.
- Removed 2 fishes and repositioned the remaining 2.
- Removed the sign from the buoy.
- Added a seagull on the buoy.
- Added an extra ladder on both spawns.
- Added more spawnpoints (each spawn has 16 now).
- Added a bunch of tree's.
- Added a lot of rocks for cover.
- Added a sun.
- Added a soundscape.
- Added a 3d skybox representing endless water.
- Extended the map border, I made it bigger, people can walk a bit in the surrounding water now.

In this map you'll spawn with a knife only, the gungame mod has to do the rest. I can make custom map versions with guns lying on the ground at request. Thats it, have fun!

A fun gg map with 3 different levels so to speak. There is a bridge in the middle, with 2 little underpasses, which are covered in glass. There is also a sewer pipe running under the map which both teams can access. There are well designed boxes and barriers. This map is a lot of fun, please leave your comments. Cheers

Map Stats

Build time = 6 Hours Compile time = 3 minutes

Map Description

This map is a small map with two spawnpoints. on either sides of the spawn points there are crates to give you cover. in the middle there is a drop sure enough to kill you if you were to fall and between the gap of the spawnpoints there is a small, creeky bridge enabling you to enter the enimy territory if you dare. on both sides of the spawnpoints there is a concrete shelter which is climbable via two ladders either side of the shelter. ontop of the shelters there are plenty of crates to hide behind. On Here would be an exellent sniping point. Good Luck And Have Fun.

Credits and Notes

**Note** Bots Dont Function properley on this map because when they come under combat they run off of the bridge. They Do Work but just somtimes. its just not recomended. Thank You For reading this and viewing the map. please comment and assess this map and if you happen to give me a low score (bellow 5/10) please post a valid reason. thank you
